The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 PCB to appoint assistant coach

Islamabad: With the high-profile home series against India beginning early next year, the Pakistan Cricket Board (PCB) has decided to appoint an assistant coach for the team. 

A PCB official said they were looking at various options and Mushtaq Ahmed, currently serving the team as a bowling consultant, was one of them. ...We are looking at appointing a long-term assistant coach with the team and Mushtaq is among the few candidates we are considering at the moment, the official said. 

The official said the boards ad-hoc committee had in principle decided to have an assistant coach. We will take a decision before the Indian series and the appointment could continue for a few series or until the next World Cup, he said. (PTI) 




